I bought this because I wanted my own copy of Chocolate but really like Finding Neverland to be much more entertaining.  These are movies without the special effects that wear you out and you only watch once then wonder why you bought them.  Good stories good actors and actresses and you can re-watch them and enjoy them like it is the first time.  A great value!

Quite a few years ago I rented the Video (!) "Finding Neverland". I absolutely fell in love with it-it is so emotional and wonderful. I believe that I have practically every Johnny Depp movie that is available. He is magnificent in both of these movies. I especially love "Finding Neverland" as it is emotional, funny and heart wrenching. Kate Winslet is perfect in this movie as well. "Chocolat" is a wonderfully romantic film-I find it to be very sensual. I love this set of films! Well Pleased!
Great buy for two films. A pleasure to watch my all time favorite actor! A nice addition to my collection.

Great double feature CD at amazing price. International cast acting out good fantasy stories with good scenery.  Vendor has good selection of movies and ships promptly.  I would recommend this vendor to family and friends.

This double disc set arrived on time and was in perfect condition.  Two amazing movies for fans of great movies, not to mention the brilliant acting including Johnny Depp, Kate Winslet, and Juliette Binoche.  Two of my favorites in one package is a great deal.

I love, love,  love this movie.  Juliette Binoche transforms her role to that of a goddess.  And chocolate becomes the currency of love and tolerance and loss and the joy of renewal.  Alfred Molina is perfection as "Mr. le Compte."  His all-knowing patrician patriarch becomes the vulnerable, needy soul with no loss of dignity.  Judi Dench manages to be tough ad funny and vulnerable as Armande.  Her relationship with grandson Luc is touching and amusing.  Len a Olin is absolutely luminous as Josephine, the abused wife. Her beauty grows with her strength. And though he does have  some dialogue as the Irish  gypsy, Roux, , Johnny Depp need not utter a word to work his magic.  His face says everything that needs to be said and then some.  The dance scene with Vianne is charmingly erotic.  I bought this movie on a disc with "Finding Neverland."  I got my money's worth.
